org.openmuc.jdlms.datatypes

Class DataObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openmuc.jdlms.datatypes.DataObject

  • public class DataObject
extends java.lang.Object
    Container class holding data about to send to the smart meter or received by the smart meter

    Either stores a Number, List of DataObjects, a byte array, BitString or a subtype CosemDateFormat.

    ALPDU (Application Layer Protocol Data Unit)

      • isComplex

        public boolean isComplex()
        Checks if the data of this container is of a complex type.

        A complex container holds one or more sub container of type DataObject as values.

        A container is of complex type if choiceIndex() returns either Data.Choices.ARRAY, Data.Choices.STRUCTURE or Data.Choices.COMPACT_ARRAY.

        Returns:
        true is the DataObject holds a List of DataObject.

      • isByteArray

        public boolean isByteArray()
        Checks if the data of this container is a byte array.

        A container is a byte array if choiceIndex() returns either Data.Choices.OCTET_STRING, Data.Choices.VISIBLE_STRING or Data.Choices.BIT_STRING.

        Returns:
        true if the data is a byte array (byte[]).

      • isBoolean

        public boolean isBoolean()
        Checks if the data of this container is a boolean.
        Returns:
        true if the data is a boolean.

      • isCosemDateFormat

        public boolean isCosemDateFormat()
        Checks if the data of this container is a CosemDateFormat object.

        A container is a calendar if choiceIndex() returns either Data.Choices.DATE_TIME, Data.Choices.DATE or Data.Choices.TIME.

        Returns:
        true if the data is a CosemDateFormat.
